headline: What Analysts Think Is Changing the Story for PayPal and Its Future Edge Over Competitors
summary: PayPal Holdings has seen a subtle recalibration in its fair value narrative, with the estimate nudging down from about $82.22 to $82.00 per share even as analysts grow more optimistic on its growth trajectory. Under the surface, expectations for revenue expansion have strengthened from roughly 6.30% to 7.50%, while a slightly lower discount rate of about 7.73% now points to a marginally reduced required return that offers modest valuation support.
